    {
      "content": "After failover",
      "pos": [
        9431,
        9445
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When enabling protection for a specific virtual machine, Site Recovery allocates networking resources as follows:",
      "pos": [
        9510,
        9623
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Site Recovery allocates an IP address for each network interface on the virtual machine from the static IP address pool defined on the relevant network for each VMM instance.",
      "pos": [
        9628,
        9802
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the administrator defines the same IP address pool that's used on the primary site for the network on the recovery site Site Recovery will allocate the same IP address that's allocated to the primary virtual machine to the replica virtual machine  The IP address is reserved in VMM but isn't set as the failover IP address.",
      "pos": [
        9806,
        10132
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The failover IP address is set just before the failover.",
      "pos": [
        10133,
        10189
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This screenshot shows the failover TCP/IP settings for the replica virtual machine (on the Hyper-V console).",
      "pos": [
        10190,
        10298
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These settings are replicated just between failover starts for the virtual machine.",
      "pos": [
        10299,
        10382
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Set IP address",
      "pos": [
        10390,
        10404
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the same IP address isn't available Site Recovery will allocate a different address from the pool.",
      "pos": [
        10471,
        10572
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After the virtual machine is enabled for protection you can use following sample script to verify the IP address that has been allocated to the virtual machine.",
      "pos": [
        10576,
        10736
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The same IP address would be set as failover IP address and assigned to the VM at the time of failover.",
      "pos": [
        10737,
        10840
      ]
    },
    {
