      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An Azure virtual machine that's an extension of the on-premises network so that applications can fail over seamlessly.",
      "pos": [
        12782,
        12900
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that when you set up your site-to-site connection in Azure, an Azure network allows you to route traffic to the on-premises location (Azure calls it local-network) only if the IP address range is different from the on-premises IP address range, because Azure doesn’t support stretching subnets.",
      "pos": [
        12903,
