      ],
      "content": "When failover is triggered and the VMs are created in the Recovery Network with the required IP address, connectivity to the VM can be established using a. This action can be scripted. As we discussed in the previous section about subnet failover, also in the case of failover to Azure routes would have to be appropriately modified to reflect that 192.168.1.0/24 has now moved to Azure.\n  ![Azure networks](./media/site-recovery-network-design/ASR_NetworkDesign9.png)",
